lines.text: You gotta - I say, you gotta keep on your toes. Toes, that is.
Let's bury - I say, let's bury the hatchet, but not in anyone's head, boy.
I just takes a step and presto, I lays an egg.
Presto, and he lays an egg. And to think for fifteen years I've been doing it the hard way.
I'll show you a chicken. A rooster, in fact.
Rooster? If I'm a roost - I say, if I'm a rooster, I hope to be struck by...
Well, let's put it another way - way, that is.
What's the gag - I say, what's the gag, son? Gag, that is.
